The paper deals with compressed sensing and phase retrieval, which are both topics in information theory (cs.IT) and signal processing (cs.SP). The use of linear programming and the natural parameter space suggests a focus on optimization (cs.LG). The paper also mentions the use of 1-bit compressed sensing, which falls under computer vision (cs.CV) and multimedia (cs.MM).
